The paper deals with the Graph Coloring Problem (GCP), which is a well-known problem in computer science and falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also proposes a new approach based on randomized heuristics, which is a common technique used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of an evolutionary algorithm, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents results based on a large benchmark of graph instances, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, falling under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
